HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1006
By Keisling
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Neal Bartlett upon his
induction into the Clay County Sports Hall of
Fame.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that this General Assembly pay tribute to those gifted athletes,
coaches, and administrators who have attained the very pinnacle of sporting achievement; and
WHEREAS, Neal Bartlett is one such legendary athlete, who was recently inducted into
the Clay County Sports Hall of Fame; and
WHEREAS, an iconic figure within the annals of both the football and basketball
programs at Celina High School from 1978 to 1981, Mr. Bartlett is considered by many to be
one of the best athletes in the school's history; and
WHEREAS, while playing basketball for four years under Head Coach Thomas Watson,
Neal Bartlett helped the Bulldogs to the District 7-A championship in his sophomore season in
1978. As a junior in 1979, he was named to the All District Tournament team; his senior
campaign saw him help defeat the State's second-ranked team, East Robertson, in the region
quarterfinals, before claiming the Region 4-A championship over Pickett County and falling 55-
56 against Sale Creek in the substate round; and
WHEREAS, Neal Bartlett's highlights on the gridiron include an 83-yard rushing
touchdown against Baxter and an 85-yard kickoff-return touchdown against Monterey, both as a
sophomore; as a senior under Head Coach Harold Watson, he helped his team advance to the
Boyce Smith Bowl against David Lipscomb, and he was also named to the All-Tri-Lakes
Conference defensive team that year; and
WHEREAS, Neal Bartlett demonstrated leadership, skill, and athleticism throughout his
athletic career, and it is fitting that we should honor him on this special occasion; now, therefore,
HJR1006
013238
- 1 -

BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Neal Bartlett upon his induction into the Clay
County Sports Hall of Fame and extend to him our best wishes for much continued success and
happiness.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
